# Public API surface (c-lib)

## Human approval required (non-negotiable)

**Any modification to the c-lib public API must be explicitly approved** by the project maintainer (or the human author of the change in review) before it is treated as final.

This includes, without exception:

- **Adding, removing, or renaming** exported symbols in **`include/api.h`** (`api_*` functions, `typedef`s, `struct` fields visible to hosts, `#define` constants that affect host contracts).
- **Changing signatures** (parameters, return types, constness) or **semantics** of any **`api_*`** entry point.
- **Resizing or reordering** **`api_options_t`** / **`api_stats_t`** / other structs that **FFI bindings** mirror (e.g. **`python_ai/engine_ctypes.py`**).
- **Documented “public” adjuncts:** updates to **`docs/api.md`** that describe new stable behavior, if they imply a new host-visible contract.

**Agent / automation behavior:** Do **not** merge or present a public API change as complete without **stating that maintainer approval is required** and, in interactive work, **confirming with the user** before altering **`api.h`** or binding-facing layouts. Internal-only changes (**`static`** helpers, **`src/*.c`** with no header export) are **not** public API changes.

## No new `api_*` without maintainer approval

- **Do not add** new **`api_*`** entry points or FFI-visible structs to **`api.h`** without **explicit maintainer approval** (see “Human approval required” above).
- **Do not** wrap **`ai_agent_complete_chat`** (or similar) as a new **`api_cloud_*`** export; keep vendor HTTP inside **`src/ai_agent.c`** and existing **`api_chat`** / **`api_chat_*`** as already declared.

**Note:** **`api.h`** already declares more than a minimal four-name list (streaming, prepare/external reply, geo, etc.). The maintainer may treat **engine init**, **chat**, **stats**, and **history** as the **priority** group for docs and new hosts — that is **not** permission to delete or break other shipped symbols without approval.

## Less API is better

- **Default bias:** Do **not** add new public functions or types unless a **host** (python_ai, c_ai, or another language binding) truly needs them and cannot use **`api.h`** + existing **`api_options_t`** / session APIs.
- **Extend before invent:** Prefer **one more field** on **`api_options_t`**, **one more value** on an existing enum, or **behavior inside** an existing **`api_*`** call over a new exported symbol.
- **Internal stays internal:** Helpers, storage details, and wire protocol belong in **`static`** functions or **`src/*.c`** only. If another **in-repo** C module needs it, use a **single** internal header under **`include/`** only when unavoidable — not a second “public” surface for apps.

## Force host-facing behavior through the public API

- **Bindings contract:** Anything **`python_ai`** / **`engine_ctypes`** must call should live on **`include/api.h`** (or the small set of headers explicitly documented in **`.cursor/rule.md`** as advanced: engine, ollama, storage for special apps).
- **No accidental exports:** Do not introduce **`extern`** helpers in headers that apps might start depending on “because they link the .so.” If it is not in **`docs/api.md`** and not meant for FFI, keep it out of the stable surface.
- **Naming:** New stable entry points use the **`api_`** prefix where appropriate; avoid parallel prefixes that duplicate **`api_*`** responsibility.

